11:
Haha... Oh, I was a fool for thinking 
I stood a chance.
19:
How could I? Well, I don't see I had any 
other choice. I'm your manager, Dia... 
And the Administrator's watchdog.
20:
It's not too late, princess... Abandon 
these people. Go back to her.
23:
Because the only thing waiting for 
traitors... is vengeance.
25:
Yes... He's quite right, my lovely little 
Diva.
35:
Administrator?! THAT thing? She's, uh... 
smaller than I imagined.
39:
Look at that wretched state you're in, 
Regis. I'd feel bad for you—if I weren't 
so positively incensed at the mess 
you've dragged Diva into.
40:
The collectors will come for you later. 
Do sit back and relax until then.
49:
Administrator, please! Don't hurt my 
friends.
51:
They haven't done anything wrong! 
And they're alive, just like—
54:
Oh, Diva. My sweet, darling Diva! How 
could you leave me so utterly alone?
55:
Was it those aliens, my heart? What 
poison have they poured into your 
ears? What fog now clouds your pure, 
naïve little mind?
62:
They've been bad—very bad. And they 
must be punished... They MUST, my 
Diva!
63: You sing for me, and me alone!
69:
Dia... is her own person. She belongs to 
no one... but herself.
74:
Why has the Watcher come to our 
world…
80:
It can't be... But wait... Where is the 
Purger?
Ahhh... Hahaha... I see!
82:
Diva, get away from them! They're 
dangerous!
Come to me, darling, and I'll see that 
they're ERASED!
89:
I don't want to go with you! I want to 
go with them... I want to leave this 
world.
94:
But that's against your 
programming...
Diva, they've contaminated you!
95:
Report to me at once! I'll rip those dirty 
thoughts from your head—
104:
That must have been a familiar... She 
knows where we are. We cannot stay 
here any longer!
108:
Haha... You've done it now. You've 
incurred the all-consuming wrath of 
the goddess.
115:
What a show! The Administrator's 
beloved canary, wooed away by a 
band of thieves—from right under her 
nose.
116:
You best move fast... because she's 
coming like a whirlwind.
119: You're all in danger... 'cause of me...
121:
Before you go... Alk, be a chum and 
promise me you'll take good care of 
my princess?
126: I will, but it won't be 'cause I promised!
134:
Heh. I must say, things have taken an 
intriguing turn.
